  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of Powerpc-Utils</title>

    <para>This package, originally pmac-utils, has issues with NewWorld macintoshes.
    The following debian patch fixes these issues and generally updates the package,
    although it also introduces a bogus warning to update the kernel headers.</para>

<screen><userinput>zcat ../&powerpcutils-patch; | patch -p1</userinput></screen>

    <para>Compile the useful programs:</para>

<screen><userinput>make nvsetenv nvsetvol</userinput></screen>

    <para>Install the package:</para>

<screen><userinput>install -m755 nvsetenv nvsetvol /usr/sbin
install -m644 nvsetvol.8 /usr/share/man/man8</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

